race.comment: Competitive affair to close out the card. Former Victorian SAVAGERY VIBE (13) is having her first run for the new stable but should find this easier than what she was contesting down south. Revved up for this with a recent trial and trust that the Gollan yard has her up to the mark for this. Can run a big race while fresh. JENCHICK BOOM (12) has a win and a second from two starts here and has really only put in one poor one in ten starts to date. Include in calculations. CINDERSEA (14) has displayed ability in all three NSW outings and looks the runner in this field with the most upside. Top-three commodity. SNITZOND (6) returned in fine fashion with a strong Toowoomba victory and gets some weight off with the claim. Can go back-to-back.
